# Configuration Guide

## Astro Configuration
The main Astro configuration is in [astro.config.ts](mdc:astro.config.ts). This file controls:
- Build settings
- Integration configurations
- Development server settings
- Build output settings

## TypeScript Configuration
TypeScript settings are in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json), including:
- Compiler options
- Module resolution
- Type checking rules
- Path aliases

## UnoCSS Configuration
UnoCSS settings are in [uno.config.js](mdc:uno.config.js), controlling:
- Custom utilities
- Theme settings
- Presets
- Transformers

## ESLint Configuration
Code quality rules are in [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs), defining:
- Code style rules
- Best practices
- TypeScript-specific rules

## Environment Configuration
Development environment is managed by:
- [mise.toml](mdc:mise.toml) - Development tools and versions
- [.node-version](mdc:.node-version) - Node.js version
- [.nvmrc](mdc:.nvmrc) - Node version manager settings

## Content Configuration
Content management settings are in [src/content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts), defining:
- Content collections
- Schema definitions
- Content validation rules

## Internationalization
Language settings are in [src/i18n.ts](mdc:src/i18n.ts), including:
- Available languages
- Default language
- Language detection rules
- Translation loading
